l requires.&#8221;&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: =
16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">All of those things fit into =
three paragraphs; he goes on for another eight. But I&#8217;ll spare you. Y=
ou get the point:&#160;</p><blockquote style=3D"border-left: 4px solid #51b=
4e9; margin: 20px 0; padding: 0;"><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-=
size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0; margin-left: 20px;"><em>=
<span>Actually, millions of human beings have had a hand in my creation, no=
 one of whom even knows more than a very few of the others&#8230; </span><s=
trong>There isn&#8217;t a single person in all these millions, including th=
e president of the pencil company, who contributes more than a tiny, infini=
tesimal bit of know-how.</strong></em></p></blockquote><p style=3D"color: r=
gb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">No=
 one involved in the process knows how to make a pencil, but all contribute=
 to the process, whether they intend to or not.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color:=
 rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">=
If that&#8217;s true of a pencil, imagine how little of the know-how that g=
oes into a solar panel or semiconductor is contributed by any single person=
=2E It must be measured in nanometers.=
