e;">Sequencing</a></em><span>.</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64)=
; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Today, a n=
umber of companies are competing to bring down the cost of sequencing and o=
pen up more use cases, which in turn will drive down the cost of sequencing=
=2E One startup, </span><a href=3D"https=
://substack.com/redirect/82944c28-d4b=
7-441d-958b-5491fe91e15e?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKb=
qOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decoration: und=
erline;">Ultima Genomics</a><span>, came out of stealth last May with an an=
nouncement that it </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/c3ea673e=
-4f61-4724-b460-bc2638c78479?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXX=
epKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decoration:=
 underline;">can deliver the $100 genome</a><span>. That&#8217;s promising,=
 but remains to be seen. You can be sure, however, that the announcement sp=
urred acceleration among competitors.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rg=
b(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">I&#=
8217;m leaving out the work of millions of people across generations, from =
Mendel to metallurgists, each of whom has played a small but important role=
=2E&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64,=20=
64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height=
: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">There isn&#8217;t a single person in all these=
 millions who contributes more than a tiny, infinitesimal bit to the progre=
ss in DNA sequencing, yet that progress flows so smoothly it&#8217;s called=
